Sto-Rox Upper Elementary Parent Tutorial
We understand that online learning is a struggle for everyone! We have just completed the orientation for our students and now we want to support the parents in this new learning adventure.

We are offering in-person Parent Help Sessions at each building to show you how to use Google Classroom on the parent side and also assist you with any questions you may have.

When: Wednesday, September 9, 2020 from 8 a.m.- 9 a.m.
Wednesday, September 9, 2020 from 7 p.m.-8 p.m.
Thursday, September 10, 2020 from 1:30-2:30
Where: SRUE Library *Limited to the first 22 people

**Masks required**

Please make an appointment if you are interested in coming for the tutorial at 412-771-3213 ext. 2000.

*More to come if needed.
*This is a Title One Event

post_text:
Staggered opening for the Sto-Rox Jr./Sr. High School:

To adhere to safety and health precautions for all, we have developed a staggered schedule where only a portion of students will be returning to the building at a time. The following schedule will be in place for students to come in and get acquainted with the technology they will be using.

Thursday, August 27, 2020- Grades 7, 9, and 11 students with last names A-K are in-person (all other students will learn virtually)

Friday, August 28, 2020- Grades 7, 9, and 11 students with last names L-Z are in-person (all other students will learn virtually)

Monday, August 31, 2020- Grades 8, 10, and 12 students with last names A-K are in-person (all other students will learn virtually)

Tuesday, September 1, 2020- Grades 8, 10, and 12 students with last names L-Z are in-person (all other students will learn virtually)

A normal school schedule will be run each day. (7:20 am - 2:13 pm)

Graduation Update: The 2020 Sto-Rox Graduation Ceremony will take place on Friday, July 10th in the Jr/Sr. High School Auditorium. Students will be limited to two guests. Masks are required and social distancing must be adhered to. For the safety of students and community, graduation will occur on a timed basis by alphabet. You are asked to arrive at your designated time and enter through the Auditorium door located on Rosamond Street. There will be no seating in the Auditorium. Please check the Sto-Rox Facebook page and school website for more information regarding designated student arrival times. This is the most up-to-date information regarding graduation. Information about the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer Program:
Families that receive SNAP or TANF should have already had their benefits issued to their EBT card. If not, you may direct families to submit an inquiry at https://www.emergencymealsurvey.com/PA. All others, cards are in the process of being issued and mailed, but due to the very large volume, the timeline is slightly delayed. Households should receive their cards by the end of July.

post_text: To the 2019-2020 graduates: Graduation will be held on July 10th at 7:00 pm. All graduating students should report to the high school cafeteria at 6 pm. Masks are recommended but not required and we are requesting all guests to bring their own chair to practice social distancing on the field. Those without chairs will be directed to the stadium seats. All guests will be asked to park in the teacher parking lot and will enter the field through the gate at that end of the stadium. There will be no entry through the courtyard. If weather causes a cancellation, we will not have a rain date. You should contact the main office to collect your diploma.

post_text:
Virtual Career Days
Week two

Tuesday will be Learn & Earn; this session will be for students 14-21 who are interested in summer employment. Thursday will be US Probation of Western PA; this is a discussion about Careers in Criminal Justice and appropriate for any age. Here are the details and registration links......

Virtual Career Day: Learn & Earn
Tuesday, May 12th @ 1:00 EST
Sophia Leissa, Learn & Earn Fellow at Partner4Work, will discuss summer employment opportunities through the Learn & Earn Program. Learn & Earn is open to young people ages 14 to 21. Teachers, counselors and parents are welcome to attend.

Register Here: https://www.eztalks.com/r/969185862

Virtual Career Day: US Probation
Thursday, May 14th @ 1:00 EST
Jessica Albert, Community Resource Specialist at the US Probation & Pretrial Services Office of Western PA, will discuss Careers in Criminal Justice. This webinar is ideal for any student 7-12. Teachers, counselors and parents are welcome to attend.

Register Here: https://www.eztalks.com/r/977827847

*Register Here: https://www.eztalks.com/r/977810146

and open to students, teachers, counselors and parents.

*Register Here: https://www.eztalks.com/r/921020

Mr. Jeffrey Robol and Mr. Tim Ayersman from Dollar Bank presented Mr. Scott Albert with a check that provides Sto-Rox Jr/Sr High School the opportunity to participate in the U Can B Program.

Entrepreneurs and businesspeople, along with the non-profit organization Building Bridges for Business, are giving local students the chance to see what life is like after high school and college.

Shown (left to right) Scott Albert, Jeffrey Robol, Tim Ayersman, Dawn Marshall and State Rep Anita Kulik.

post_text:
Students in Ms. Finklang’s Honors English class accepted the challenge to write essays for the 2020 Western PA Student Essay Contest. This contest was sponsored by Stop the Violence Pittsburgh’s African American Programs and the topic for the class essay was “The Voting Rights Act of 1965”. Mallory Key was selected as 2nd place winner of the contest. She was presented a trophy and a check for three hundred dollars by William Marshall of “Stop the Violence”. Congratulations to Sto-Rox student, Mallory Key!

Shown (left to right): Sam Weaver, William Marshall, Mallory Key, Chris Captline, Joe Herzing and Deb Finklang
